snippet.textDisplay:
The dimples on the golf ball are specifically implemented because they create turbulant flow(crazy flow essentially with no one specific direction) with on coming air on the surface of the golf ball. Turbulant flow is more optimal in golf because it reduces air resistance on the ball and allows your ball to travel further than if it was smooth. The other type of flow is laminar which is seen more on smooth surfaces and has fluid travel in a more organized fashion.
P.s. I love your videos⭐⭐⭐

snippet.textDisplay:
Your lip gloss also started out as white, then had color added.

My mother was the youngest of her siblings, and they told her that donut holes were poison. She believed them and left the best parts of the donut!

The watch pocket was retained by jeans makers because they kept change from falling out. Later, people wouldn't buy jeans unless they had the pocket. When I was a kid, we wouldn't buy shirts without the little thingies on the back where we would hang them. The bigger kids would pull them out until parents began demanding other parents pay for new shirts or repair them.

Those were the days!
